# Git Commit Standards

## Co-authored-by Tag

**NEVER** include `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any similar AI attribution in commit messages.

### ❌ BAD
```
fix: resolve TypeError in message processing

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
```

### ✅ GOOD
```
fix: resolve TypeError in message processing

- Remove duplicate group chat check
- Add null safety for chatGuid
```

## Commit Message Format

Follow conventional commits format:

```
<type>: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

### Types
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code refactoring
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks
- `test`: Test changes

### Examples

```
feat: add file attachment support for iMessage

- Upload files to Manus via presigned URLs
- Support multiple attachments per message
- Add error handling for failed uploads
```

```
fix: prevent duplicate message processing

Fixes #42

- Add message deduplication in worker
- Clear processed message cache every 5 minutes
```

## Issue References

When fixing issues, reference them in the commit footer:

```
fix: resolve authentication timeout

Fixes #123

- Increase connection timeout to 60s
- Add retry logic for failed auth
```
